<h2>What These Trends Mean for Businesses</h2>
<p><strong>The big picture:</strong> SEO is splitting into two disciplines. Traditional SEO still drives traffic through organic rankings. Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) builds visibility inside AI-generated answers. Businesses that excel at both will dominate search in 2026 and beyond.</p>
<p><strong>For small and local businesses:</strong>
- Local searches still drive high-intent traffic. The local 3-pack and Google Business Profile remain strong
- Informational blog content now serves brand building more than direct traffic generation
- Reviews, citations, and local schema markup matter more than ever for <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO</a>
- Commercial keywords ("best [service] in [city]") hold up better than informational ones
- Consistent publishing builds the topical authority that both Google and AI models reward</p>
<p><strong>The risk of ignoring these trends:</strong> Businesses that continue optimizing only for traditional organic rankings will see declining traffic as AI Overviews expand. Those that adapt early will capture visibility in both traditional and AI-driven search results.</p>
