<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>Is SEO dead in 2026?</strong></p>
<p>No. Organic search still drives 53% of all website traffic. What changed is how results appear. AI Overviews reduce clicks for informational queries, but commercial, transactional, and local searches still generate strong traffic. The businesses ranking on page 1 still capture the majority of clicks in their market.</p>
<p><strong>How are AI Overviews affecting SEO traffic?</strong></p>
<p>AI Overviews reduce organic CTR by 58% on queries where they appear. They trigger on 48% of all searches, primarily informational ones. Commercial and local queries are less affected. The net impact depends on your keyword mix. Sites focused on informational content see the biggest declines. Sites focused on commercial and local content see minimal impact.</p>
<p><strong>What is Generative Engine Optimization (GEO)?</strong></p>
<p>GEO is the practice of optimizing content to appear in AI-generated search results. AI Overviews, ChatGPT responses, Perplexity answers, and Gemini summaries all pull from web content. GEO focuses on structured data, content depth, authoritative sourcing, and machine readability. See our <a href="/blog/geo-vs-seo/">GEO vs SEO guide</a> for a full comparison.</p>
<p><strong>What is the best SEO strategy for 2026?</strong></p>
<p>Combine traditional SEO with GEO. Publish consistent, high-quality content with named authors and cited sources. Add schema markup to every page. Build brand presence beyond your website. Focus keywords on commercial and local intent where clicks still happen. Monitor AI citation rates alongside traditional ranking metrics.</p>
<p><strong>How do I prepare my site for AI search?</strong></p>
<p>Ensure AI crawlers can access your content. Add an <a href="/blog/create-llms-txt/">llms.txt file</a>. Implement JSON-LD schema markup. Structure content with clear headings and direct answers in the first 100 words. Include specific data points with citations. Build topical authority through consistent publishing in your core subject area.</p>
